gzstream
------------------------------------------
Gzstream is a small C++ library, basically just a wrapper, that provides the
functionality of the zlib C-library in a C++ iostream.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libgzstream-devel-1.5+git20171107-1bl1
  libgzstream1-1.5+git20171107-1bl1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1
  zlib0-1.3.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cmake-4.1.2-1
  cygport-0.37.3-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.1-1
  zlib-devel-1.3.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/kanedo/gzstream

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/kanedo/gzstream.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack gzstream-1.5+git20171107-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./gzstream-1.5+git20171107-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gzstream-1.5+git20171107-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/gzstream-1.5+git20171107-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgzstream1-1.5+git20171107-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgzstream-devel-1.5+git20171107-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(gzstream)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/gzstream.README
  /usr/share/doc/gzstream/COPYING.LIB
  /usr/share/doc/gzstream/README
  /usr/share/doc/gzstream/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/gzstream/logo.gif

(libgzstream1)
  /usr/bin/cyggzstream-1.dll

(libgzstream-devel)
  /usr/include/gzstream.h
  /usr/lib/libgzstream.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/gzstream.pc

